===Etymology===
From {{bor|en|tvl||lit=eight standing together}} in reference to the eight inhabited islands of Tuvalu, although Tuvalu consists of nine islands. The ninth island was inhabited in 1949. Compare to {{cog|map-pro|*walu|t=eight}}.

